</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Commitments
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In February 2014, the Company entered into a noncancelable operating lease agreement (the Lease) for certain office space with a lease term from July 2014 through December 2019 with a renewal option for an additional five years. In May 2015, the Company entered into a first amendment to the Lease (the First Lease Amendment) for additional office space starting in September 2015 through September 2020. The First Lease Amendment also extended the term of the Lease to September 2020. The monthly base rent under the Lease and the First Lease Amendment will increase approximately 3% annually from $32,784 in 2015 to $39,268 in 2020. Future minimum payments under this noncancelable operating lease total $2.0 million at December 31, 2015.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Rent expense was $339,053, $243,832 and $167,998 for the years ended December&#160;31, 2015, 2014 and 2013, respectively.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In July 2010, the Company entered into a stock purchase agreement with Pfizer, pursuant to which the Company acquired all of the outstanding stock of Idun. Under the agreement, the Company may be required to make payments to Pfizer totaling $18.0 million upon the achievement of specified regulatory milestones.
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	Spin-off of Idun Pharmaceuticals, Inc.
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In January 2013, the Company spun off its subsidiary Idun to the Company&#8217;s stockholders. Prior to the spin-off, rights relating to emricasan were distributed to the Company by Idun pursuant to a distribution agreement. The spin-off was conducted as a dividend of all of the outstanding capital stock of Idun to the Company&#8217;s stockholders. As a result, the Company no longer holds any capital stock of Idun.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	F-17

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:4.54%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="CNAT-10K_20151231_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU89">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	In c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	onnection with the spin-off, the Company contributed $0.5 million to Idun to provide for Idun&#8217;s initial working capital requirements. The assets remaining in Idun at the time of the spin-off consisted of cash, intellectual property rights and license and c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	ollaboration agreements unrelated to emricasan. Other than the cash of $0.5 million, none of the assets held by Idun had any historical carrying value at the time of the spin-off. As a result, the Company recognized a reduction in equity as a result of the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	spin-off of $0.5 million, representing the carrying value of Idun in the Company&#8217;s financial statements at the time of the spin-off.

<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	(1)
</SUP>
	Net loss per share is computed independently for each quarter and the full year based upon respective shares outstanding; therefore, the sum of the quarterly net loss per share amounts may not equal the annual amounts reported.&nbsp;&nbsp;

	Subsequent to the year ending December 31, 2015 through the date of this filing, the Company sold 930,101 shares of common stock pursuant to the Sales Agreement at an average price per share of $2.78 and received net proceeds of $2.6 million, after deducting offering related transaction costs and commissions.

<EFX_EXHIBIT_10>
<A NAME="FIS_EXHIBIT_10"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:13PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-INDENT:0%;">
	Exhibit 10.11
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:7.69%;MARGIN-RIGHT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:0%;">
	EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	THIS EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT (this &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Agreement
</FONT>
	&#8221;) is entered into by and between Conatus Pharmaceuticals Inc., a Delaware corporation (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Company
</FONT>
	&#8221;), and Charles J. Cashion (&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Employee
</FONT>
	&#8221;), and shall be effective as of December 17, 2008 (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Effective Date
</FONT>
	&#8221;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	WHEREAS, the Company and Employee are parties to that certain Founder&#8217;s Agreement dated as of July 13, 2005, as amended by that certain First Amendment to Founder&#8217;s Agreement dated as of January 15, 2006 (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Prior Agreement
</FONT>
	&#8221;); and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	WHEREAS, the Company and Employee desire to replace the Prior Agreement with this Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual promises herein contained, the parties agree as follows:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	1.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Definitions
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;As used in this Agreement, the following terms shall have the following meanings:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(a)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Board
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Board
</FONT>
	&#8221; means the Board of Directors of the Company.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(
</FONT>
	b)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Cause
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Cause
</FONT>
	&#8221; means any of the following:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(i)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	the commission of an act of fraud, embezzlement or dishonesty by
</FONT>
	Employee that has a material adverse impact on the Company or any successor or affiliate thereof;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(ii)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	a conviction of, or plea of &#8220;guilty&#8221; or &#8220;no contest&#8221; to, a felony by
</FONT>
	Employee or any crime involving fraud, misappropriation, embezzlement or moral turpitude;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(iii)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	any unauthorized use or disclosure by
</FONT>
	Employee of confidential information or trade secrets of the Company or any successor or affiliate thereof that has a material adverse impact on any such entity;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(iv)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	Employee&#8217;s gross negligence, insubordination or material violation of any duty of loyalty to the Company or any other material misconduct on the part of Employee;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(v)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	Employee&#8217;s ongoing and repeated failure or refusal to perform or neglect of Employee&#8217;s duties as required by this Agreement, which failure, refusal or neglect continues for fifteen (15) days following Employee&#8217;s receipt of written notice from the Board or the Company&#8217;s Chief Executive Officer (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	CEO
</FONT>
	&#8221;) stating with specificity the nature of such failure, refusal or neglect; or
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:23.08%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(vi)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	Employee&#8217;s breach of any material provision of this Agreement;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<A NAME="CNAT-EX1011_886_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU2">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	provided
</FONT>
	,
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	however
</FONT>
	, that prior to the determination that &#8220;Cause&#8221; under this Section 1(b) has occurred, the Company shall (w) provide to Employee in writing, in reasonable detail, the reasons for the determination that such &#8220;Cause&#8221; exists, (x) other than with respect to clause (v) above
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:6PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage96"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	which specifies the applicable period of time for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	to remedy his or her breach, afford
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	a reasonable opportunity to remedy any such breach
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(if such breach is capable of being remedied)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	, (y) provide
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	an opportunity to be heard prior to the final decision to terminate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8217;s employment hereunder for such &#8220;Cause&#8221; and (z) make any decision that such &#8220;Cause&#8221; exists in good faith.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	The foregoing definition shall not in any way preclude or restrict the right of the Company or any successor or affiliate thereof to discharge or dismiss Employee for any other acts or omissions, but such other acts or omissions shall not be deemed, for purposes of this Agreement, to constitute grounds for termination for Cause.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(c)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Change of Control
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Change of Control
</FONT>
	&#8221; means and includes each of the following:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(i)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	a transaction or series of transactions (other than an offering of common stock of the Company to the general public through a registration statement filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission) whereby any &#8220;person&#8221; or related &#8220;group&#8221; of &#8220;persons&#8221; (as such terms are used in Sections 13(d) and 14(d)(2) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Exchange Act
</FONT>
	&#8221;), and the rules thereunder) (other than the Company, any of its subsidiaries, an employee benefit plan maintained by the Company or any of its subsidiaries or a &#8220;person&#8221; that, prior to such transaction, directly or indirectly controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with, the Company) directly or indirectly acquires beneficial ownership (within the meaning of Rule 13d-3 under the Exchange Act) of securities of the Company possessing more than fifty percent (50%) of the total combined voting power of the Company&#8217;s securities outstanding immediately after such acquisition; or
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(ii)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	during any period of two consecutive years, individuals who, at the beginning of such period, constitute the Board together with any new director(s) (other than a director designated by a person who shall have entered into an agreement with the Company to effect a transaction described in subsections (
</FONT>
	i)&#160;or (iii)&#160;of this Section 1(c)) whose election by the Board or nomination for election by the Company&#8217;s stockholders was approved by a vote of at least two-thirds of the directors then still in office who either were directors at the beginning of the two year period or whose election or nomination for election was previously so approved, cease for any reason to constitute a majority thereof; or
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(iii)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	the consummation by the Company (whether directly involving the Company or indirectly involving the Company through one or more intermediaries) of a merger, consolidation, reorganization, or business combination, a sale or other disposition of all or substantially all of the Company&#8217;s assets, or the acquisition of assets or stock of another entity, in each case, other than a transaction
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<A NAME="CNAT-EX1011_886_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU3">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(A)which results in the Company&#8217;s voting securities outstanding immediately before the transaction continuing to represent (either by remaining outstanding or by being converted into voting securities of the Company or the person that, as a result of the transaction, controls, directly or indirectly, the Company or owns, directly or indirectly, all or substantially all of the Company&#8217;s assets or otherwise succeeds to the business of the Company (the Company or such person, the &#8220;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Successor Entity
</FONT>
	&#8221;)) directly or indirectly, at least fifty percent
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage97"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	50%
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	of the combined voting power of the Successor Entity&#8217;s outstanding voting securities immedia
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	tely after the transaction, and
</FONT>
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	(B)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	after which no person or group beneficially owns voting securities representing
</FONT>
	fifty percent (50%) or more of the combined voting power of the Successor Entity;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	provided
</FONT>
	,
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	however
</FONT>
	, that no person or group shall be treated for purposes of this paragraph (iii) as beneficially owning fifty percent (50%) or more of combined voting power of the Successor Entity solely as a result of the voting power held in the Company prior to the consummation of the transaction; or
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(iv)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	the Company&#8217;s stockholders approve a liquidation or dissolution of the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	For purposes of subsection (i) above, the calculation of voting power shall be made as if the date of the acquisition were a record date for a vote of the Company&#8217;s stockholders, and for purposes of subsection (iii) above, the calculation of voting power shall be made as if the date of the consummation of the transaction were a record date for a vote of the Company&#8217;s stockholders.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Notwithstanding the foregoing, a transaction shall not constitute a &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Change of Control
</FONT>
	&#8221; if: (i) its sole purpose is to change the state of the Company&#8217;s incorporation; (ii) its sole purpose is to create a holding company that will be owned in substantially the same proportions by the persons who held the Company&#8217;s securities immediately before such transaction; (iii) it constitutes the Company&#8217;s initial public offering of its securities; or (iv) it is a transaction effected primarily for the purpose of financing the Company with cash (as determined by the Board in its discretion and without regard to whether such transaction is effectuated by a merger, equity financing or otherwise).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(
</FONT>
	d)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Code
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Code
</FONT>
	&#8221; means the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended from time to time, and the Treasury Regulations and other guidance issued thereunder.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(e)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Good Reason
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee&#8217;s resignation for &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Good Reason
</FONT>
	&#8221; means Employee&#8217;s resignation following the occurrence of any of the following events or conditions without Employee&#8217;s written consent:
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(i)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	a material diminution in Employee
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#AUTO;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	&#8217;s
</FONT>
	authority, duties or responsibilities;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(ii)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	a material diminution in Employee
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#AUTO;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	&#8217;s
</FONT>
	base compensation, except in connection with a general reduction in the base compensation of the Company&#8217;s or any successor&#8217;s or affiliate&#8217;s personnel with similar status and responsibilities;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(iii)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	a material change in the geographic location at which Employee must perform his or her duties (and the Company and Employee agree that any requirement that Employee be based at any place outside a 50-mile radius of his or her place of employment as of the Effective Date, except for reasonably required travel on the Company&#8217;s or any successor&#8217;s or affiliate&#8217;s business that is not materially greater than such travel requirements prior to the Effective Date, shall be considered a material change); or
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage98"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<A NAME="CNAT-EX1011_886_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU4">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	i
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	v)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	any
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	other action or inaction that constitutes a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	material breach by the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	or any successor or affiliate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	of its obligations to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	under this Agreement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	.
</FONT>
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	Notwithstanding the foregoing, Good Reason shall only exist if Employee shall have provided the Company with written notice within ninety (90) days of the initial occurrence of any of the foregoing events or conditions, and the Company or any successor or affiliate fails to eliminate the conditions constituting Good Reason within thirty (30) days after receipt of written notice of such event or condition from Employee.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#AUTO;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	&#8217;s
</FONT>
	termination by reason of resignation from employment with the Company for Good Reason shall be treated as involuntary.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee&#8217;s resignation from employment with the Company for &#8220;Good Reason&#8221; must occur within twelve (12) months following the initial occurrence of one of the foregoing events or conditions.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(f)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Permanent Disability
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee&#8217;s &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Permanent Disability
</FONT>
	&#8221; shall be deemed to have occurred if Employee shall become physically or mentally incapacitated or disabled or otherwise unable fully to discharge his or her duties hereunder for a period of ninety (90) consecutive calendar days or for one hundred twenty (120) calendar days in any one hundred eighty (180) calendar-day period.&nbsp;&nbsp;The existence of Employee&#8217;s Permanent Disability shall be determined by the Company on the advice of a physician chosen by the Company and the Company reserves the right to have the Employee examined by a physician chosen by the Company at the Company&#8217;s expense.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(g)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Stock Awards
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Stock Awards
</FONT>
	&#8221; means all stock options, restricted stock and such other awards granted pursuant to the Company&#8217;s stock option and equity incentive award plans or agreements and any shares of stock issued upon exercise thereof, and any founders&#8217; stock issued to Employee in connection with the formation of the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	2.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Employment Period
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp; During the term of Employee&#8217;s employment hereunder (the &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Employment Period
</FONT>
	&#8221;), Employee shall be considered an employee of the Company. The Company and Employee acknowledge that Employee&#8217;s employment during the Employment Period will be at-will, as defined under applicable law, and that Employee&#8217;s employment with the Company during the Employment Period may be terminated by either party at any time for any or no reason, with or without notice.&nbsp;&nbsp;If Employee&#8217;s employment during the Employment Period terminates for any reason, Employee shall not be entitled to any payments, benefits, damages, awards or compensation other than as provided in this Agreement.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	3.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:72PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Services to Be Rendered
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<A NAME="CNAT-EX1011_886_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU5">
</A>
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Duties and Responsibilities
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall serve as Senior Vice President Finance and Chief Financial Officer of the Company of the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the performance of such duties, Employee shall report directly to the CEO
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	and shall be subject to the direction of the CEO and to such limits upon Employee&#8217;s authority as the
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	CEO
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	may from time to time impose.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event of the CEO&#8217;s incapacity or unavailability, Employee shall be subject to the direction of the Board or its designee.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee hereby consents to serve as an officer and/or director of the Company or any subsidiary or affiliate thereof without any additional salary or compensation, if so requested by the Board or the CEO.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee&#8217;s primary place of work shall be the Company&#8217;s facility in San Diego, California, or such other location within San
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<HR STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS;WIDTH:100%;">
<A NAME="eolPage99"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Diego County as may be designated by the Board or the CEO from time to time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall also render services at such other places within or outside the United States as
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	the Board or the CEO may direct from time to time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall be subject to and comply with the policies and procedures generally applicable to employees of the Company to the extent the same are not inconsistent with any term of this Agreement.
</FONT>
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(b)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Exclusive Services
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall at all times faithfully, industriously and to the best of his or her ability, experience and talent perform to the satisfaction of the Board and the CEO all of the duties that may be assigned to Employee hereunder and shall devote substantially all of his or her productive time and efforts to the performance of such duties.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	4.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Compensation and Benefits During Employment Period
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;During the Employment Period, the Company shall pay or provide, as the case may be, to Employee the compensation and other benefits and rights set forth in this Section 4.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(a)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:108PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Base Salary
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company shall pay to Employee a base salary of $236,250 per year, payable in accordance with the Company&#8217;s usual pay practices (and in any event no less frequently than bi-monthly).&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee&#8217;s base salary shall be subject to review annually by and at the sole discretion of the Board or its designee.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(b)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Annual Bonus
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall be eligible to earn, for each fiscal year of the Company ending during the Employment Period, an annual cash performance bonus (an &#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Annual Bonus
</FONT>
	&#8221;) based on Employee&#8217;s and/or the Company&#8217;s attainment of objective financial or other operating criteria established by
<FONT STYLE="LETTER-SPACING:-0.1PT;">
	the Board or its designee
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon full attainment of the aforementioned criteria, as determined by
<FONT STYLE="LETTER-SPACING:-0.1PT;">
	the Board or its designee,
</FONT>
	the Annual Bonus will be equal to thirty percent (30%)
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	of Employee&#8217;s then-current base salary actually paid for such fiscal year.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Annual Bonus shall be paid to Employee by the Company between January 1
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	st
</SUP>
	and March 15
<SUP STYLE="FONT-SIZE:85%; VERTICAL-ALIGN:TOP">
	th
</SUP>
	of the calendar year following the end of the fiscal year to which such Annual Bonus relates.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee&#8217;s receipt of an Annual Bonus shall be conditioned on Employee&#8217;s continued employment with the Company on the date such Annual Bonus is paid.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Annual Bonus shall be pro-rated for any partial fiscal year during the Employment Period.&nbsp;&nbsp;As of the Effective Date, the Company&#8217;s fiscal year ends on December 31.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event of any change to the Company&#8217;s fiscal year, the aforementioned financial or other operating criteria established by the Board or its designee for purposes of determining Employee&#8217;s Annual Bonus shall be adjusted in a manner mutually agreeable to the Company and Employee so as not to disadvantage either party.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<A NAME="CNAT-EX1011_886_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU6">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	(c)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Benefits
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall be entitled to participate in benefits under the Company&#8217;s benefit plans and arrangements, including, without limitation, any employee benefit plan or arrangement made available in the future by the Company to its senior executives, subject to and on a basis consistent with the terms, conditions and overall administration of such plans and arrangements. The Company shall have the right to amend or delete any such benefit plan or arrangement made available by the Company to its senior executives and not otherwise specifically provided for herein.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company&#8217;s failure to continue provide Employee with benefits substantially equivalent (in terms of benefit levels and/or reward opportunities) to those provided to Employee under each material employee benefit plan, program and practice of the Company as in effect immediately prior to the Effective Date, except in connection with a general reduction in the benefits of the Company&#8217;s or any successor&#8217;s or affiliate&#8217;s personnel
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;

	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE:10PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	with similar status and responsibilities, shall constitute a material breach of this Agreement by the Company.
</FONT>
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(d)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Expenses
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Company shall reimburse Employee for reasonable out-of-pocket business expenses incurred in connection with the performance of his or her duties hereunder, subject to (i)&#160;such policies as the Company may from time to time establish, (ii)&#160;Employee furnishing the Company with evidence in the form of receipts satisfactory to the Company substantiating the claimed expenditures, (iii) Employee receiving advance approval from the CEO in the case of expenses for travel outside of North America, and (iv) Employee receiving advance approval from the CEO in the case of expenses (or a series of related expenses) in excess of $10,000.&nbsp;&nbsp;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#AUTO;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	Any amounts payable under this Section 4(d) shall be made in accordance with Treasury Regulation Section 1.409A-3(i)(1)(iv) and shall be paid on or before the last day of
</FONT>
	Employee
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#AUTO;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	&#8217;s taxable year following the taxable year in which
</FONT>
	Employee
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#AUTO;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	incurred the expenses.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amounts provided under this Section 4(d) during any taxable year of
</FONT>
	Employee
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#AUTO;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	&#8217;s will not affect such amounts provided in any other taxable year of
</FONT>
	Employee
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#AUTO;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	&#8217;s, and
</FONT>
	Employee
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;COLOR:#AUTO;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	&#8217;s right to reimbursement for such amounts shall not be subject to liquidation or exchange for any other benefit.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(
</FONT>
	e)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Paid Time Off; Vacation
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall be entitled to such periods of paid time off (&#8220;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	PTO
</FONT>
	&#8221;) each year as provided under the Company&#8217;s PTO policy and as otherwise provided for senior executive officers;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	provided
</FONT>
	that Employee shall be entitled to at least three (3) weeks paid vacation per year.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(f)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Equity Plans
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall be entitled to participate in any equity or other employee benefit plan that is generally available to senior executive officers, as distinguished from general management, of the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;Except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, Employee&#8217;s participation in and benefits under any such plan shall be on the terms and subject to the conditions specified in the governing document of the particular plan.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:15.38%;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(g)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Acceleration of Vesting of Stock Awards
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(
</FONT>
	i)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	The vesting and/or exercisability of one hundred percent (100%) of Employee&#8217;s outstanding Stock Awards shall be automatically accelerated on the date of a Change of Control.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(
</FONT>
	ii)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	Subject to Section 5(c), if Employee&#8217;s employment is terminated by the Company without Cause or by Employee for Good Reason, the vesting and/or exercisability of each of Employee&#8217;s outstanding Stock Awards shall be automatically accelerated on the date of termination as to the number of Stock Awards that would vest over the twelve (12) month period following the date of termination had Employee remained continuously employed by the Company during such period.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(
</FONT>
	iii)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	The foregoing provisions are hereby deemed to be a part of each Stock Award and to supersede any less favorable provision in any agreement or plan regarding such Stock Award.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	5.
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Termination of Employment Period and Severance
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall be entitled to receive benefits upon termination of the Employment Period only as set forth in this Section 5.
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	6
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">

	&nbsp;
</P>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Termination Without Cause or For Good Reason
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	I
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	f
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8217;s employment is terminated by the Company without Cause or by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	for Good Reason,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	shall be entitled to receive, in lieu of any severance benefits to which
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	may otherwise be entitled under any severance plan or program of the Company, the benefits provided below:
</FONT>
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(i)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	the Company shall pay to
</FONT>
	Employee his or her fully earned but unpaid base salary, when due, through the date of termination at the rate then in effect, plus all other amounts to which Employee is entitled under any compensation plan or practice of the Company at the time of termination;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:7.69%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(ii)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	subject to Sections 5(c), 5(g) and 5(h) and Employee&#8217;s continuing compliance with Section 6, Employee shall be entitled to receive Employee&#8217;s monthly base salary as in effect immediately prior to the date of termination for the twelve (12) month period following the date of termination, payable in a lump sum no later than sixty (60) days following the date of Employee&#8217;s termination of employment; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:7.69%;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
	(iii)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
	subject to Sections 5(c), 5(g) and 5(h)
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	and Employee&#8217;s continuing compliance with Section 6, for the period beginning on the date of termination and ending on the date which is twelve (12)
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	full months following the date of termination (or, if earlier, the date on which the applicable continuation period under
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act of 1985, as amended
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	(&#8220;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	COBRA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">
	&#8221;)
</FONT>
	expires), the Company shall pay for and provide to Employee
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	and his or her eligible dependents who were covered under the Company&#8217;s health insurance plans immediately prior to the date of termination healthcare insurance benefits substantially similar to those provided to Employee and his or her eligible dependents immediately prior to the date of termination, including, if necessary, paying the costs associated with continuation coverage pursuant to COBRA.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-SIZE:13PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	(b)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	Termination for Cause, Voluntary Resignation Without Good Reason, Death or Permanent Disability
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;If Employee&#8217;s employment is terminated by the Company for Cause, by Employee without Good Reason or as a result of Employee&#8217;s death or Permanent Disability, the Company shall not have any other or further obligations to Employee (or his or her estate) under this Agreement (including any financial obligations) except that Employee (or his or her estate) shall be entitled to receive (i) Employee&#8217;s fully earned but unpaid base salary, through the date of termination at the rate then in effect, and (ii) all other amounts or benefits to which Employee is entitled under any compensation, retirement or benefit plan or practice of the Company at the time of termination in accordance with the terms of such plans or practices, including, without limitation, any continuation of benefits required by COBRA or applicable law.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, if Employee&#8217;s employment is terminated by the Company for Cause, by Employee without Good Reason or as a result of Employee&#8217;s death or Permanent Disability, all vesting of Employee&#8217;s unvested Stock Awards previously granted to him or her by the Company shall cease and none of such unvested Stock Awards shall be exercisable following the date of such termination.&nbsp;&nbsp;The foregoing shall be in addition to, and not in lieu of, any and all other rights and remedies which may be available to the Company under the circumstances, whether at law or in equity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">

</FONT>

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

</FONT>

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">

<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">

<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Release
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="COLOR:#000000;">

</FONT>

	in a form reasonably acceptable to the Company
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	and any applicable revocation period
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	applicable to such Release
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	shall have expired
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such Release shall specifically relate to all of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8217;s rights and claims in existence at the time of such execution, including any claims related to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8217;s employment by the Company and his or her termination of employment, and shall exclude any continuing obligations the Company may have to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	following the date of termination under this Agreement or any other agreement providing for obligations to survive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	Employee
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&#8217;s termination of employment.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(
</FONT>
	d)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Exclusive Remedy
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Except as otherwise expressly required by law (e.g., COBRA) or as specifically provided herein, all of Employee&#8217;s rights to salary, severance, benefits, bonuses and other amounts hereunder (if any) accruing after the termination of Employee&#8217;s employment shall cease upon such termination.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event of a termination of Employee&#8217;s employment with the Company, Employee&#8217;s sole remedy shall be to receive the payments and benefits described in this Section 5.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, Employee acknowledges and agrees that he or she is not entitled to any reimbursement by the Company for any taxes payable by Employee
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	as a result of the payments and benefits received by Employee
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	pursuant to this Section 5, including, without limitation, any excise tax imposed by Section 4999 of the Code.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<A NAME="CNAT-EX1011_886_HTM_OLE_LINK5">
</A>
<A NAME="CNAT-EX1011_886_HTM_OLE_LINK6">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
	(
</FONT>
	e)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	No Mitigation
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	shall not be required to mitigate the amount of any payment provided for in this Section 5 by seeking other employment or otherwise, nor shall the amount of any payment or benefit provided for in this Section 5 be reduced by any compensation earned by Employee
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	as the result of employment by another employer or self-employment or by retirement benefits;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	provided
</FONT>
	,
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	however
</FONT>
	, that loans, advances or other amounts owed by Employee
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	to the Company may be offset by the Company against amounts payable to Employee
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	under this Section 5;
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	provided
</FONT>
	,
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	further
</FONT>
	, that, as provided in Section 5(a), Employee&#8217;s right to continued healthcare and life insurance
<FONT STYLE="FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
	benefits following his or her termination of employment will terminate on the date on which the applicable continuation period under COBRA expires.&nbsp;&nbsp;
<FONT STYLE="FONT-SIZE:13PT;">
	&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:15.38%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	(f)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Return of the Company&#8217;s Property
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;If Employee&#8217;s employment is terminated for any reason, the Company shall have the right, at its option, to require Employee to vacate his or her offices prior to or on the effective date of termination and to cease all activities on the Company&#8217;s behalf.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon the termination of his or her employment in any manner, as a condition to the Employee&#8217;s receipt of any post-termination benefits described in this Agreement, Employee shall immediately surrender to the Company all lists, books and records of, or in connection with, the Company&#8217;s business, and all other property belonging to the Company, it being distinctly understood that all such lists, books and records, and other documents, are the property of the Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employee shall deliver to the Company a signed statement certifying compliance with this Section 5(f) prior to the receipt of any post-termination benefits described in this Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;TEXT-INDENT:7.69%;">
<A NAME="CNAT-EX1011_886_HTM__AEIOULASTRENDEREDPAGEBREAKAEIOU9">
</A>
	(g)
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN-LEFT:36PT;">
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;">
	Short-Term Deferral
</FONT>
	.&nbsp;&nbsp;This Agreement is not intended to provide for any deferral of compensation subject to Section 409A of the Code, and, accordingly, the severance payment payable under Section 5(a)(ii) shall be paid no later than the later of:&nbsp;&nbsp;(i) the fifteenth
</P>
<P STYLE="TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;MARGIN-TOP:12PT;MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:12PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	8
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:11PT;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT;TEXT-INDENT:0%;FONT-SIZE:8PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;FONT-VARIANT: NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</P>
